<paragraph id="F4420662FFA40718FF7D17C42EDC4122" blockId="19.[132,775,750,855]" pageId="19" pageNumber="218">
DISTRIBUTION AND ECOLOGY. — 
<taxonomicName id="33FD7DE1FFA40718FE3717DA2C984172" authorityName="H. Perrier" authorityYear="1952" box="[462,641,752,775]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ebenaceae" genus="Diospyros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="19" pageNumber="218" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tetraceros">
<emphasis id="C689DA70FFA40718FE3717DA2C984172" box="[462,641,752,775]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="218">Diospyros tetraceros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in dry riverine forest in northwestern 
<collectingCountry id="8CEA46F2FFA40718FE4E16202C334157" box="[439,554,778,802]" name="Madagascar" pageId="19" pageNumber="218">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
in the Ambato-Boeny Region in the basin of the Betsiboka river (
<bibRefCitation id="906C7B93FFA40718FDD2160E2EAE4122" author="Madagascar Catalogue" firstAuthor="Madagascar Catalogue" pageId="19" pageNumber="218" refId="ref13623" refString="MADAGASCAR CATALOGUE 2020. - Catalogue of the plants of Madagascar. Missouri Botanical Garden, St. Louis &amp; Antananarivo. http: // legacy. tropicos. org / Project / Madagascar" type="url" year="2020">
<collectingCountry id="8CEA46F2FFA40718FDD2160E2C874149" box="[555,670,804,828]" name="Madagascar" pageId="19" pageNumber="218">Madagascar</collectingCountry>
Catalogue 2020
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BCE755E9FFA40718FF7D16472F8741D5" pageId="19" pageNumber="218" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="F4420662FFA40718FF7D16472F8741D5" blockId="19.[132,775,877,929]" pageId="19" pageNumber="218">
PHENOLOGY. — 
<taxonomicName id="33FD7DE1FFA40718FED016452FC441F3" authorityName="H. Perrier" authorityYear="1952" box="[297,477,879,902]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ebenaceae" genus="Diospyros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="19" pageNumber="218" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tetraceros">
<emphasis id="C689DA70FFA40718FED016452FC441F3" box="[297,477,879,902]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="218">Diospyros tetraceros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been recorded in flower in January, and in fruit in June.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BCE755E9FFA40718FF7D169D2CB7461A" pageId="19" pageNumber="218" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="F4420662FFA40718FF7D169D2CB7461A" blockId="19.[132,776,951,1135]" pageId="19" pageNumber="218">
CONSERVATION STATUS. — 
<taxonomicName id="33FD7DE1FFA40718FE5916932C4041A5" authorityName="H. Perrier" authorityYear="1952" box="[416,601,953,976]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ebenaceae" genus="Diospyros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="19" pageNumber="218" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tetraceros">
<emphasis id="C689DA70FFA40718FE5916932C4041A5" box="[416,601,953,976]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="218">Diospyros tetraceros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a geographic range in the form of an AOO of 
<quantity id="3305AB87FFA40718FE3E16F92FE3419E" box="[455,506,979,1003]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="19" pageNumber="218" unit="km" value="8.0">8 km</quantity>
2. It is not known from any protected areas, and is threatened by fire, forest clearing for agriculture, and collection of firewood and construction materials. With respect to the principal threats of fire and forest clearing for agriculture, 
<taxonomicName id="33FD7DE1FFA40718FF0211172F694621" authorityName="H. Perrier" authorityYear="1952" box="[251,368,1085,1108]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ebenaceae" genus="Diospyros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="19" pageNumber="218" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tetraceros">
<emphasis id="C689DA70FFA40718FF0211172F694621" box="[251,368,1085,1108]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="218">D. tetraceros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
exists at two locations, and can therefore be assessed as Endangered [EN B2ab(iii)] (
<bibRefCitation id="906C7B93FFA40718FDDF117D2CB9461A" author="IUCN" box="[550,672,1111,1135]" firstAuthor="IUCN" pageId="19" pageNumber="218" refId="ref13513" refString="IUCN 2012. - IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria: Version 3.1. Second edition. IUCN, Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, United Kingdom." type="book" year="2012">IUCN 2012</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="BCE755E9FFA40718FF7D11BF2FF84725" pageId="19" pageNumber="218" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="F4420662FFA40718FF7D11BF2ED646D8" blockId="19.[132,775,1173,1360]" box="[132,207,1173,1199]" pageId="19" pageNumber="218">NOTES</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F4420662FFA40718FF7D119C2FF84725" blockId="19.[132,775,1173,1360]" pageId="19" pageNumber="218">
<taxonomicName id="33FD7DE1FFA40718FF7D119C2F5246BA" authorityName="H. Perrier" authorityYear="1952" box="[132,331,1206,1231]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ebenaceae" genus="Diospyros" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="19" pageNumber="218" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tetraceros">
<emphasis id="C689DA70FFA40718FF7D119C2F5246BA" box="[132,331,1206,1231]" italics="true" pageId="19" pageNumber="218">Diospyros tetraceros</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has not been collected since 1908. It can be distinguished from other members of the Squamosa group by its small leaves and calyx lobes forming 4 horn-like projections and sinuses strongly revolute, nearly concealing the exterior surface of the calyx cup.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
